@metroApi_HostAddress = https://metrobackend-tq8v.onrender.com

### Test 1: Create a new product (without image)
POST {{metroApi_HostAddress}}/api/Products
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Test LED Light",
  "description": "A test LED light for image testing",
  "price": 99.99,
  "features": ["Energy Efficient", "Long Lasting"],
  "applications": ["Commercial", "Industrial"],
  "advantages": ["Low Maintenance", "Bright Output"],
  "subcategoryId": 1
}

### Test 2: Get all products to see the new product
GET {{metroApi_HostAddress}}/api/Products
Accept: application/json

### Test 3: Upload image for product (replace {productId} with actual ID from Test 1)
POST {{metroApi_HostAddress}}/api/Image/upload/1
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test-image.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./test-image.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### Test 4: Get product again to see image URL
GET {{metroApi_HostAddress}}/api/Products/1
Accept: application/json

### Test 5: Get product image directly
GET {{metroApi_HostAddress}}/api/Image/product/1
Accept: image/*

### Test 6: Get image by filename (replace {filename} with actual filename from upload response)
GET {{metroApi_HostAddress}}/api/Image/{filename}
Accept: image/*

### Test 7: Delete image (replace {filename} with actual filename)
DELETE {{metroApi_HostAddress}}/api/Image/{filename}
Accept: application/json
